# Documentation maintenance

Applies when editing schema, routes, API clients, or app routing.

- New or changed REST route: add/update **one row** in [docs/api.md](mdc:docs/api.md).
- Model or relation change: update [docs/domain.md](mdc:docs/domain.md).
- New route/page or API client module: update [docs/frontend.md](mdc:docs/frontend.md).
- Auth/FX/architecture change: update [docs/architecture.md](mdc:docs/architecture.md) only if behavior changed.

Skip doc updates for trivial changes (typo, CSS-only, comment-only).

Do **not** expand `golden-rule.mdc` or `project-context.mdc` per feature — only when global conventions change.

Keep entries short (table rows); no full JSON examples in docs.
